<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1048" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1048">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 125.8273/68.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Canada</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-26">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your May 26, 11 a.m. Mr. Silliman himself may draw for necessary
                                funds. Department would be glad to have him come to Washington as
                                soon as he feels physically able to make the trip.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>